This bug requires actual CPU hotplug operations (taking a CPU offline) which kSTEP doesn't support. The bug occurs in the `idle_task_exit()` → `mmdrop()` path during CPU offline, after RCU has stopped monitoring the dying CPU. This cannot be triggered through kSTEP's task/tick control interface.

